    "created_at": "2015-09-28T17:12:51Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-28T17:12:51Z",
    "body": "Can confirm on Fedora 23. Running Slack alone results in Xorg eventually running out of client connections. Running Atom alone never resulted in the problem though which makes me think that either Atom leaks much slower, Atom does not hit the particular usage pattern that leads to a bug or the problem is specific to Slack and is not necessarily related to Electron.\n"
