    "created_at": "2015-10-09T09:06:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-09T09:06:55Z",
    "body": "Looks like Slack fixed the issue in the latest 1.2.4 version - a new notification doesn't spawn a ghost Xorg connection anymore. There are almost no changes in the notification scripts and the wrapper object, but they did upgrade to 0.33.6, so I guess the issue was in Electron, but fixed since 0.30.5.\n\nSo that's a wrap. :)\n"
